Infinity Nikki Personal Data and Privacy Policy
Last Updated: [2024-12-02]
Effective Date:[2024-12-02]
Preamble
Infinity Nikki Personal Data and Privacy Protection Policy
(hereafter referred to as "Privacy Policy” or “Policy”) is
made by and between you (hereafter referred to as “you/user”) and Infold Pte. Ltd. (hereafter referred to as “Infold” or “we”) whose registered office is at6 Raffles Quay, #14-06, Singapore.
Infold takes the protection of your personal data and privacy very seriously. To safeguard your legal rights when using the services we provide, including your interactions with us, registration, and use of our games as well as registration and use of other products or services we offer (hereafter referred to as "services"), we have created this Privacy Policy. It aims to explain how we collect, use, store, share and transfer such data when you use our services. Additionally, it outlines the ways we provide you to access to, update, control and protect this data. Specifically, if you use our services in South Korea,
인폴드 유한책임회사 개인정보 수집 및 이용 안내
shall apply; if you use our services in Japan,
『インフィニティニキ』プライバシーポリシー
shall apply.
WE STRONGLY RECOMMEND THAT YOU READ THIS PRIVACY POLICY CAREFULLY AND IN ITS ENTIRETY, FULLY, PAYING PARTICULAR ATTENTION TO THE TERMS MARKED IN BOLD. PLEASE MAKE CHOICES THAT YOU DEEM APPROPRIATE IN ACCORDANCE WITH THE GUIDELINES OUTLINED IN THIS PRIVACY POLICY. IF YOU DO NOT AGREE TO THE CONTENT OF THIS POLICY, IT MAY IMPACT OUR ABILITY TO PROVIDE OUR SERVICES EFFECTIVELY OR TO DELIVER THE EXPECTED SERVICES.
If you are a child (the specific age is determined according to the definition of “child” age in the laws of the country or region where you reside, for example, under 14 years old in South Korea, or under 13 years old in some other countries and regions) or do not meet the age requirement for using Infold game services in your country/region, you are not allowed to use our Services. If your age exceeds the age of a child stipulated in the laws of your country and region but you are a minor (the specific age is determined according to the definition of “adult” age in the laws of the country or region where you reside, for example, under 19 years old in South Korea, and under 18 years old in some countries and regions) or are otherwise ineligible as stated above,, you must read this Policy accompanied by your parents or legal guardians and use our Services only after obtaining the consent of your parents or guardians to all this Policy. These requirements also apply to all modifications or changes to this Privacy Policy.
PLEASE BE AWARE THAT WE DO NOT COLLECT PERSONAL DATA FROM MINOR USERSunder the age of 13 OR USERS WHO DO NOT MEET THE AGE REQUIREMENT SPECIFIED BY YOUR COUNTRY/REGION TO USE THE GAME SERVICE. IF YOU ARE THE GUARDIAN OF A RELEVANT MINOR AND YOU FIND THAT YOUR MINOR HAS USED OUR SERVICES AND SUBMITTED THEIR PERSONAL DATA, PLEASE INSTRUCT THEM TO STOP USING OUR SERVICES IMMEDIATELY AND INFORM US PROMPTLY SO THAT WE CAN TAKE APPROPRIATE MEASURES ACCORDINGLY. WE ALSO PROVIDE A REMINDER IN THE ANNEX OF THIS POLICY ACCORDING TO THE PERSONAL DATA PROTECTION REQUIREMENTS OF DIFFERENT COUNTRIES/REGIONS. IF YOUR COUNTRY/REGION IS LISTED IN THE ANNEX, PLEASE READ THE RELEVANT REGULATIONS IN DETAIL.
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or other relevant matters after reading the entire Policy, please contact us through the channels set in the Section “Contact Us” herein, and we will respond to you as soon as possible.
This Privacy Policy will provide you with information on:
I. How We Collect and Use Your Personal Information
II. How We Use Cookies and Similar Technologies
III. How We Process, Share, Transfer, and Disclose Your Personal Information
IV. How We Store and Protect Your Personal Information
V. Your Rights to Manage Personal Information
VI. Protection of Minor Information
VII. Update of the Privacy Policy
VIII. Miscellaneous
IX. Contact Us
I. How We Collect and Use Your Personal Information
According to the requirement of relevant laws and regulations or for the functionality of specific services, we collect, store and use the following information about you. The lawful collection, storage, and use serve the purpose of providing or optimizing our services, or user experience and ensuring the security of your account.
You understand and agree that: some individual services may necessitate enabling specific access permissions on your device to facilitate the collection and use of information related to those permissions. You also understand and agree that failing to provide such information may hinder your ability to register as a user, enjoy specific services provided by us, or achieve the intended results of using the relevant services.
For users of our game products, the game itself may be unavailable if the necessary information is not provided to build a user profile and identify the user, depending on the operation of the game system.
Should we use your information for purposes other than those described below, we will provide further explanation and seek your consent.
1. Personal Information You Provide
(1) When you register, log in, and undergo identity verification, you provide your Infold account (such as the email address or third-party account you used to register or log in to your Infold Account) as credentials for logging into the game, creating your username and password. The information you provide will be used to determine your age when using our services. Providing false information will result in the inability to use our services or may subject you to corresponding restrictions during service usage. You agree that we may collect your online identification information (including account number, password and IP address) and information on your commonly used personal device (including hardware serial number, hardware model, MAC address of the device, OS type, OS version, device name, carrier). This information will be used to identify you as our user and provide you with basic services. Please note that if you use an Infold Account registered or logged with third-party accounts (such as PlayStationNetwork account, Apple Account, Google Account, Facebook Account, etc.) to access Infold Games, subject to applicable laws and with your consent, we may obtain information generated or shared through your use of a third-party account to register/log in to your Infold Account, which may include  your unique identifier, account name, personal avatar and list of friends of such third-party account.
This information is used to store your registration and login information, enabling you to log in to our system on different devices. If you do not consent to the authorization of such information, you will not be able to use your third-party account to register or log in to your Infold Account and thereby access our products and services.
We need to remind you that you can only register as our user and access our services when you provide true and accurate information as described above. Failure to provide such information will result in the inability to log in or use all or part of our services.
(2) When you set to customize your character information, you may submit or edit your nicknames, personal taglines, and avatars.
(3) Information you submit through our customer service or for participating in the activities or questionnaire surveys held or conducted by us, including your name, gender, mobile phone number, telephone number, address, educational attainment, occupation, and personal income. We would like to remind you in particular that the submission and modification of the above information may be subject to special rules of the relevant interface If the aforementioned rules are inconsistent with the rules of this Privacy Policy, we will obtain your consent separately. If you choose not to participate in such activities or questionnaire surveys, or not to provide the above information to our customer service personnel, your access to other services will not be affected.
(4) In certain services, to facilitate the delivery of goods or services to you, you are required to provide the personal information of the recipient, including name, delivery address, postal code, contact number, and payment status. Specifically, we may share some of your information with third-party logistics or delivery parties during the shipping and delivery process in order to ensure safe, smooth, and accurate delivery of goods or services to you. Failure to provide such information will prevent the completion of the relevant delivery service. However, this will not affect your normal use of other features within our services.
(5) information you share with other parties through our services, and information you provide to us and store when you use our services.
2.Your information Shared by Other Parties
(1) Your information shared by other parties when they use our services.
(2) We may obtain information generated or shared by you when you use a third-party partner’s products or services. Please read the user agreement or privacy policy of the third-party partner’s product or service carefully.
3.  Your Information We Obtain
When you use our services, we may collect the following information based on the following usage patterns:
(1) In order to ensure your normal use of our services, maintain the proper functioning of the game’s basic features, optimize product, performance, enhance your gaming experience, and protect your account security, we may collect information related to your device or software. This includes the device identifier provided by your mobile device, web browser or other programs used to access our services (for example, Android ID, GAID for Android; IDFV, IDFA for iOS; motherboard serial number, CPUID, product ID, hard drive serial number, Machine GUID for PC; DUIDs for PlayStation; the validity, reset availability by the user, and acquisition method may vary for different identifiers). The unique device identification information is used solely during your use of the services we provide and is essential for service provision. Additionally, we collect device MAC address, device name, device settings and environment, device manufacturer, device time zone, device type, device model, device version, device serial number,
OS type and version, system start up time (mobile device only), system activation time (iOS only)
, IP address
, carrier information,
mntID (iOS only), network type (Wi-Fi/5g/4g/3g/2g; wired network for PC), Wi-Fi status, Wi-Fi MAC address,
Log information (Network diagnostic logs),
application ID, client version,
installer name, hardware and software feature information,
hardware model, hardware serial number (SN), SD card data (internal/external SD card capacity, list of file names in SD card application cache directory), application name and version, SDK version,
screen resolution and size (or device resolution),
language region and country,
battery and power status (mobile device only), CPU architecture information, timestamp, whether root/jailbreak, memory size and remaining memory, Google Advertising ID (Android only), emulator information (Android only), device landscape and vertical screen information, memory module information (PC only), graphics card information (PC only), whether to enable auxiliary functions (Android only), Baseband version (mobile device only), screen brightness (mobile device only), analog positioning switch (mobile device only), whether to enable ADB (Android only), SIM card status (mobile device only), acceleration sensor.
(2) When you interact with other players in the game through text, pictures, and other means, we will collect and store the information you send. This is done for the purpose of filtering pornographic, violent, political, or abusive content, as well as malicious advertisements and other inappropriate materials. The aim is to create a clean and safe gaming environment.
(3) When you use our services, we may collect your game log data, including your login logs, item logs, game battle logs, purchase logs, activity logs, upgrade logs and friend logs. This allows you to review your gaming history in the client, and the data will be used for statistical analysis in-game operations, addressing customer complaints, conducting anti-cheat analyses aimed at optimizing the gaming experience. Moreover, to enhance your gaming experience, we may synchronize the aforementioned data with the subsequent versions of the game or our other products you use.
(4) When you make purchases within the services provided by Infold, we will collect your
top-up records and your transaction records
. This is done to facilitate your review of transaction records and maximize the protection of your virtual property. Top-up records and transaction records are considered sensitive information. The collection of this information is necessary for us to provide consumption services, and transactions cannot be completed without such information.
(5) When you contact us, we may collect your
communication or call records
, including the contents or the contact information you leave. This is done to facilitate communication with you, help you resolve a problem, or record the resolution and outcome of the relevant issue.
(6) When you copy information from our products for sharing or receive shared information within our products, we need to locally access
your device’s clipboard
to read the information for the purposes of benefits, event participation, and sharing. We will only read information relevant to our services for verification and will not store such information. We will not collect any unrelated information from your clipboard.
(7) In order to ensure the security of your game account and create a fair, sound and safe gaming environment, we will collect your
information from your device (such as ID, serial number, manufacturer, device name, type and version, model, and style of the device), device identifier [for example, board ID (motherboard UUID), CPUID, product ID, hard drive serial number, Machine GUID , for PC],
memory module information (PC only), graphics card information (PC only), online identification information, network type, carrier information, game channel sources, battery and power status (mobile device only), whether to enable auxiliary functions (Android only), Baseband version (mobile device only), system activation time (mobile device only), screen brightness (mobile device only), analog positioning switch (Android only), whether to enable adb (Android only), and SIM card status (mobile device only). This information will be used to combat activities that may undermine the fair gaming environment or interfere with the normal operation of our game services (for example, such information may be used to detect piracy, screen plugins, and anti-cheat).
(8) Device permissions: During your use of our services, we will request permissions to access your system in specific business scenarios (the specific permissions may vary depending on the model and system version of the device you are using). This is to facilitate the collection and use of the corresponding information and enable the corresponding product functions and business scenarios. We will seek your consent before obtaining permission, and you can choose whether to authorize it or not. These system permissions include:
n Android
a.  Notification permissions: Notifications may include alerts, sounds, and icons and these settings can be configured in the app settings. We will use your notification permissions when you enable push notifications (for activities like energy recovery, event notifications, weekly missions, and background playback). Specifically, in some versions of the operating system, you may need to enable the precise alarm clock permission, otherwise, you may not be able to use the push function normally.
b. External storage rights: We will read and write your external storage rights when you use the in-game photo function (such as saving pictures and screenshots to your device), and send photos to customer service.
c. Camera permissions: We will use your camera permissions when you use QR code, and send photos to customer service.
d. Front-end service permissions: We will obtain your front-end service permissions when you use the download feature.
n iOS
a.  Notification permissions: Notifications may include alerts, sounds, and icons and these settings can be configured in the app settings. We may use your notification permissions when you enable push notifications (for activities like energy recovery, event notifications, weekly missions, and background playback).
b. Album access: we may use your album access when you use the in-game photo function (such as saving pictures and screenshots to your device), and send photos to customer service.
c. Camera access: We may use your camera access when you send photos to customer service.
d. Device network access: we may use your device network access during login, updates, service usage, network environment security checks, network connection status, and network speed measurement.
e. Microphone permissions: We may use your microphone permissions when recording with the camera during your interaction with customer service.
You may manage (enable/disable) the aforementioned permissions at any time on the System Settings page of your device.
Please note that: by enabling any permission, you authorize us to collect and use the relevant information to provide you with the corresponding services. Disabling any permission withdraws, the corresponding authorization, and as a result, we will no longer collect and use the relevant information based on such permission, making it impossible to provide you with the services corresponding to such permission. However, your decision to disable any permission will not affect our previous collection and use of information based on your authorization.
Please be aware that the access names may differ from one terminal to another due to variations in terminal devices and different operating systems. If you need to disable the permission enabled for using the above specific functions, most mobile devices will support your requirement. Refer to or contact the service provider of your mobile device for specific methods (for example, if your terminal device supports it, you may manage the aforementioned permission on the System Settings page of your terminal device at any time). If you have any questions, feel free to contact us through the channels set forth in the“Contact Us” section of this Privacy Policy.
4. We May Send Notifications to You
(1)
When you use our services, we may contact you by phone or sending you emails, text messages, information or push notifications.
You can follow our relevant prompts on your device, and we will send you the information described in this paragraph with your prior consent. If you no longer wish to receive this information you may choose to unsubscribe by following our relevant prompts on your device.
(2) We may send services-related announcements to you when necessary (for example, when a given service will be suspended due to system maintenance). You may not unsubscribe from any services-related announcements which are not advertisements.
(3) We will push your account updates, etc. to you through the system notifications of your device. You can choose to turn off our notifications on your device or select the information you wish to receive through the notification settings function we provide.
5. We may collect and use certain personal information without your authorization and consent in compliance with the relevant laws, regulations, and national standards in the country where you use our services, as well as to meet the request of judicial authorities and law enforcement agencies.
6. Notice regarding When You Disclose and Share Information
A number of our services allow you to disclose or share information about yourself not only within the game you used but also with all users of the service. For example, information you upload or post on our services (including your publicly available personal information and lists you create), your responses to information uploaded or posted by others and log data related to such data (such as friend’s relationships, level, ranking). Other users of our services may also share information about you (including log data). In particular, our sharing feature is designed to make it easy for you to share information about the game with other users, and you can make that shared information available as you like. As long as you do not delete the shared information, it will remain in the public domain. Even if you delete the shared information, it may still be independently cached, copied, or stored by other users or third parties not under our control, or kept in the public domain by other users or such third parties.
Therefore, please carefully consider the content of the information that you make public, upload, post and communicate through our services. In some cases, you may control the range of users entitled to view the information you share through the privacy settings of some of our services. If you want to remove your information from our services, please contact us to confirm how to do so, and any such removal will require verification of your identity.
II. How We Use Cookies and Similar Technologies
We, or our third-party partners, may collect and use your information through cookies, web beacons and other similar technologies, and store such information. We use our own cookies, web beacons and other similar technologies for the following purposes:
1. Remember your identity. For example, cookies and web beacons help us to identify you as our registered user or store other information you provide about yourself.
2. Analyze your use of our products or services. We may use cookies and web beacons to understand the activities you engage in while using our services.
3. Our products and services may contain cookies, web beacons and other similar technologies placed by our third-party partners. These technologies may collect non-personally identifiable information about you to analyze how users use those services or evaluate the effectiveness of advertising services. We strictly require our third-party partners to adhere to the provisions of this Privacy Policy. You can refuse or manage cookies, web beacons, or similar technologies through your browser settings. However, please note that disabling cookies, web beacons, or other similar technologies, may not impact your ability to enjoy the corresponding service experience, and some services may not function properly.
III.  How We Share, Transfer, and Disclose Your Personal Information
1. To ensure the stable operation of Infold Game Services or to achieve related functionalities, we may integrate features provided by third parties or collaborate through other means to fulfill the aforementioned purposes. The purpose, categories or use of the third party’s collection and processing of personal information, along with rules for personal information protection and exit mechanism, are governed by the third party’s privacy policies or relevant statement. We recommend checking the applicable third party’s privacy policies before use to understand how, why and to what extent the third party collects and uses users’ information, as well as its legal responsibilities. If the third party does not provide a dedicated privacy policy, we may provide a link to their official website to assist you in understanding their specific practices. Please note that third-party content may alter their personal information processing practices due to version upgrades, policy changes, or other reasons. You should refer to the official announcements of the third party for the most accurate and up-to-date information.
We may share your personal information with third parties, specifically including:
(1) Cloud service providers: Support data storage and basic maintenance;
