2. Necessary Sharing with Our Affiliates: To enable us to provide integrated services through the unified Infold account system and assist you in logging in and managing various products and services, your personal information of Infold Account (such as the email address or third-party account you used to register or log in to your Infold Account, avatar, nickname and personal profile) may be shared between us and our affiliates as required. Some of the Infold Game Services may be supported by our affiliates. To provide and optimize these services, we may share your personal information with our affiliates to achieve the data processing purposes stated in this Privacy Policy. In such cases, we will only share the necessary personal information for the purposes and within the scope outlined in this Privacy Policy.
Specifically, we will share your information only for lawful, legitimate, necessary, specific, and explicit purposes. If we or our affiliates share your personal information with third parties, we will ensure that these third parties use your information in compliance with this Privacy Policy and other appropriate confidentiality and security measures, or we will require them to re-seek your authorized consent.
3. Transfer. We will transfer your personal information only when:
(1) you expressly consent;
(2) required by laws and regulations or relevant authorities;
(3) in the event of a merger, consolidation, asset transfer, or any other similar transactions as our business continues to grow, we may transfer your personal information as a part of such transactions. We will inform you through push notifications, announcements or other means, and ensure that your personal information continues to be protected, or request the new managers to continue protecting your personal information in accordance with relevant laws and regulations, meeting the standard described in this Privacy Policy.
3. Disclosure. We will disclose your personal information only when:
(1) you expressly consent;
(2) required by the laws and regulations or relevant authorities.
4. Cases in which your prior consent is not required, including when:
(1) We may share, transfer or disclose your personal information without your consent in compliance with the relevant laws, regulations, and national standards of the territory where you use our products and services, as well as the writs of execution issued by administrative or judicial authorities.
(2) You acknowledge and agree that the information we collect may be de-identified and used for big data analysis. “De-identify” means that the information has been stripped of elements relevant to you, rendering it impossible to identify or restore to your personal information. We may publicly disclose and share with our partners information that has undergone statistical processing, ensuring information anonymity. This information will be used to understand how users interact with our services and to communicate general usage trends to the public.
IV. How We store and Protect your Personal Information
1. We will store your information only as long as necessary to fulfill the purpose described in this Privacy Policy, except:
(1) when required by the laws, regulations or regulatory authorities in the location where you use our services;
(2) for reasonable and necessary purposes to safeguard the public interest or to protect the personal rights, property safety, or other legitimate interests of our customers, ourselves, our group companies, our users or employees.
2. To provide you with the highest quality of service possible, our group adheres to diversification and globalization strategies, with subsidiaries located around the world. According to the service contract between you and us, your personal information may be processed on servers located outside your place of residence when necessary. Regardless of the server’s location, we will take appropriate measures to protect your rights in accordance with this Privacy Policy. The servers for these services are located in:
Frankfurt, Germany
Singapore
Virginia, USA
Tokyo, Japan
3.We will continually work to enhance our services. During these efforts, the server locations mentioned above may be adjusted and changed to further optimize our services.
4. Infold operates globally in the gaming business, and we have suppliers all over the world. We may access some of your information from anywhere, adhering to the principles of necessity, minimization, and anonymization. You acknowledge and agree that our support team, engineering team, and other teams around the world may access and process your information from locations other than your place of residence. The information we collect or share with third-party partners may also be stored and processed on our third-party SDK servers located in the United States, Germany, Japan and Singapore. Additionally, your information can be accessed from outside your location by our support, engineering and other teams worldwide, including Singapore.
5. If we terminate the services or operations, we will promptly cease the collection of your personal information promptly. We will notify you in advance, as required by the relevant laws and regulations. Following the termination, we will delete or anonymize your personal information unless otherwise required by relevant laws, regulations and regulatory authorities.
6. We will delete or anonymize your personal information if you request to delete your account, voluntarily delete your information or after a certain necessary period of time, unless a specific retention period is required by the laws and regulations where the server of your registered account is located.
7. If the information we collect needs to be transferred across borders within our group, we will ensure that such transfer is complies with laws, regulations and the requirements of the country where the information originates. This will be done and in accordance with the stipulations of relevant regulatory authorities to provide adequate protection for your personal information. We will de-identify and anonymize your personal information to ensure security and confidentiality. Additionally, we ensure that the region where the information is received has the same level of information protection capability as your region.
8. We will take reasonable and necessary security protection measures conforming to industry standards, to reduce the risk of loss, misuse, unauthorized access or disclosure of information. For example, in some products or services, we will use encryption technology (such as SSL) to protect your personal information. However, you understand that, due to technical limitations and various malicious means that may exist, we cannot guarantee 100% security of your information, even if we have done our utmost to strengthen our security measures. Moreover,
you understand that the system and communications network you use to access our services may experience issues beyond our control.
9. When a personal information security incident occurs, we will promptly inform you in accordance with relevant laws and regulations. This notification will include the basic information about the incident, its possible impact, the measures we have taken or will take to address it, recommendations on what you can do to prevent and reduce risks, available remedies, etc. Additionally, we will notify you promptly about the incident by email, letter, phone calls, push notifications, or other suitable means. If individual notices to personal information subjects are challenging, we will publish announcements in a reasonable and effective manner. We will also proactively report our handling of the personal information security incident as required by the regulatory authorities.
V. Your Rights to Manage Personal Information
We understand your concerns regarding your personal information and make every effort to ensure that you have the right to access, correct, delete, and revoke authorization for your personal information. This ensures you have full control to safeguard your privacy and security. Your rights include:
1. Right of Access
You have the right to access the personal information you have provided to us, such as avatar, nickname, player number, motto and rankings, according to the relevant instructions (or settings) of our services. If you encounter any issues accessing or intend to access other unavailable personal information described above, you may contact us through the contact information provided in this Privacy Policy.
2. Right to Correct or Modify
When you find the personal information you provide is inaccurate, incomplete or update needed, you may correct/modify your personal information when using our services.
(1) For certain personal information, we offer operational settings on the relevant function pages of the game.  You can directly make corrections or modifications. For instance, to correct or modify your avatar in the game, please follow these steps: Pear-Pal→click on the avatar→click the Edit button.
(2) If you encounter difficulties while exercising the aforementioned rights, or if online correction or modification services are currently inaccessible, you have the right to correct or modify the inaccurate or incomplete information. This is subject to identify verification, and the correction or modification should not compromise the objectivity and accuracy of the information. In certain circumstances, particularly when the information is inaccurate, you can request us to correct or modify your information via our feedback, error reporting or customer service, unless otherwise required by laws and regulations. However, for security and identification reasons, certain initial registration information submitted during registration may not be modifiable.
3. Right to Delete
You may request the deletion of your personal information directly unless it has been anonymized or is required by laws and regulations, including in cases where:
(1) The purpose of processing personal information has been achieved or no longer exists, or there is another legal ground;
(2) Our handling of your personal information violates any laws or regulations;
(3) We collect or use your personal information without your consent;
(4) Our handling of your personal information violates the agreement with you;
(5) You delete your game account;
(6) We terminate services and operations.
If we decide to respond to your request for deletion, we will also notify the entities that have obtained your personal information from us and request their prompt deletion, unless otherwise required by the laws and regulations, or if these entities are independently authorized by you. When you delete your information from our service system, we may not delete the corresponding information from the backup system immediately but will do so at the time when the backup is updated.
4. Right to Revoke All or Part of Your Authorization
As mentioned above, certain functions of our services require your device permissions, including notification, camera, etc., as set forth in Section I “How We Collect and Use Your Personal information ”. You have the option to withdraw or cease your ongoing authorization for these permissions at any time. Updating the version will not alter the status of previously set permissions without your explicit consent. Additionally, you can permanently revoke the authorization for us to collect your personal information by deleting your account. Upon withdrawal of authorization, we will no longer be able to provide you with the corresponding services. However, please note that your decision to withdraw such authorization will not affect our prior handling of your information based on your initial authorization.
5. Right to Delete Your Account
You can request the deletion of your game account through our customer service personnel or other means we have publicized. Once your game account is deleted,  you will no longer be able to use our services with that account. All accumulated but unconsumed rights and interests of the game account, as well as all future overdue benefits and other rights and interests, will be erased. Contents, information, data and records associated with the game account will be deleted or anonymized. Please note that once your game account is deleted, it cannot be restored. For more information on the process and conditions of deleting “Infinity Nikki” game accounts, please contact our customer service.
6. Right to Request Copies of Your Personal Information
You have the right to request copies of your personal information by contacting us at any time via the contact information provided in this Privacy Policy. We will respond to your request within fifteen working days.
7. Right to Constrain Automated Decision-making in Information Systems
In certain business functions, we may rely on non-human automated decision-making mechanisms, including information systems, algorithms, etc. If these decisions significantly impact your legitimate rights, you have the right to request an explanation, and we will provide appropriate remedies.
8. How We Address Your Requests for the aforementioned Rights
We will respond to your requests within fifteen working days while verifying your identity as a user. If you have any concerns during the process of your personal information, you may contact us via the contact information provided in “Contact us”. However, we may be unable to respond to your requests if prohibited by legal writs issued by administrative or judicial authorities in the territory where you use our services.
VI. Protection of Minor Information
Please note that we do not collect personal information of child (the specific age is determined according to the definition of “child” age in the laws of the country or region where you reside, for example, under 14 years old in South Korea, or under 13 years old in some other countries and regions). If you are the guardian of a relevant minor who has used our services and submitted their personal information, please instruct them to stop using our services immediately and inform us promptly so that we can take appropriate measures accordingly. Please refer to “Your Rights to Manage Personal Information”. Our customer service personnel may verify your relationship with the minor as needed. After such verification, we will assist you in deleting such information and corresponding game account.
If we are notified that we have collected personal information of a child without the consent of a guardian, we will promptly impose restrictions on the account and delete the relevant personal information.
VII. Update of the Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy periodically, and such updates shall be considered as a part of this Privacy Policy.
If these revisions lead to a significant reduction of your rights under this Privacy Policy, we will notify you by prominently displaying the revisions on our homepage, sending you an e-mail, or providing other forms of notification. In such case, your continued use of our services implies your agreement to be bound by the updated terms.
VIII. Miscellaneous
1. This Privacy Policy applies to all our services, except for certain specifically expressed services. These specific services will be governed by distinct personal information protection statements or rules.
The personal information protection statements or rules for these certain services will provide more detailed information on how we use your information in those services.
They form an integral part of this Privacy Policy.
If there is any inconsistency between any personal information protection statements or rules and this Privacy Policy, the former shall prevail.
2. Except as otherwise provided in this Privacy Policy, the terms used herein shall have the same meanings as those defined in other publicly available documents published by us.
3. The headings of this Privacy Policy are for convenience and readability purposes only, and do not affect the meaning or interpretation of any provisions in the text.
4. This Privacy Policy shall be governed by and construed under the laws of Singapore excluding its conflict of law principles. The
Convention on Contracts for the International Sale of Goods
will not apply. You agree and acknowledge that all disputes relating to this Agreement or Infold shall first be resolved by peaceful negotiation between the parties (any dispute requiring negotiation shall be notified to Infold in writing in accordance with the contact information provided in this Agreement) . If a solution to the dispute cannot be effectively reached after thirty days of negotiation, any claims or legal actions between you and Infold shall be referred to Singapore International Arbitration Centre (SIAC) for arbitration which shall be conducted in accordance with such commission’s arbitration rules. The arbitral award is final and binding upon both parties. If the above arbitration terms are not enforceable on any dispute, both parties agree that such dispute shall be brought to a court in Singapore. You hereby consent to, and waive all defenses of lack of personal jurisdiction and/or forum non-convenience with respect to venue and jurisdiction, whether by arbitration or judicial judgment. Subject to applicable laws and regulations, both parties confirm that any dispute resolution proceedings, whether in arbitration or court, will be conducted only on an individual basis and not a class or representative action. If you do not accept these terms, please terminate your use of our services or send us a written notice of your desire to opt out of arbitration within thirty days.
5. Severability
If any provision herein is held to be invalid or declared illegal, or unenforceable for any reason, such provision shall be severed and deleted from this Privacy Policy. The remainder of this Privacy Policy shall remain unaffected and continue in force and effect. However, if a class action or arbitration waiver is held to be invalid, unenforceable, or illegal, you agree that such waiver may be inseverable. In other words, under no circumstances may any litigation proceeding be conducted on a class basis without our prior express written consent.
6. No Assignment
You may not assign, transfer, charge, or subcontract, whether by operation of law or otherwise, all or any of your rights or obligations hereunder without our express prior written consent. Otherwise, we may, at our sole discretion, terminate our provision of any services to you without further notice. If such a restriction on assignment is unenforceable under the laws of your country/region of residence or place of residence, this Privacy Policy shall remain binding upon you and your successors. Notwithstanding the foregoing, we reserve the right to assign, charge, or subcontract all or any of our rights or obligations hereunder at any time.
7. Infold’s failure to exercise, delay in exercising or partial exercise of any right under this Privacy Policy or applicable laws shall not be deemed a waiver of such right, nor shall it prevent Infold from exercising such right in the future.
8. The term “affiliate” as used herein, refers to any entity that directly or indirectly controls, is controlled by, or is under common control with Infold.
9. Infold may translate this Privacy Policy into other languages.
10. In addition to any other restrictions set forth herein, Infold shall not be liable for any delay in performance or non-performance caused by events beyond Infold’s reasonable control, such as acts of government authorities, acts of nature or other events not reasonably controllable by herein.
11. You acknowledge that you have voluntarily read and accepted this Privacy Policy, and you do not anticipate receiving any compensation beyond what is explicitly provided herein.
12. If this Privacy Policy conflicts with local laws in your country or region of residence, the local laws will take precedence.
IX. Contact Us
1. We have established a dedicated department for personal information protection in compliance with this Privacy Policy. If you have any questions, comments or suggestions about this Privacy Policy, our privacy measures, or matters relating to your personal information, you may contact us by sending an email to dpo@infoldgames.com.
